The Steelers started their regular season, against the [[2008 Houston Texans season|Houston Texans]], in front of 64,001&nbsp;spectators at [[Heinz Field]] in Pittsburgh. The Steelers drove the ball 52&nbsp;yards on their opening drive, with their biggest gain coming on a 17-yard run from quarterback [[Ben Roethlisberger]]. [[Willie Parker]] scored a touchdown at 5:44 of the opening quarter and added a second touchdown in the following quarter. After a [[LaMarr Woodley]] interception the Steelers extended their lead to 21&nbsp;points when Roethlisberger completed a 13-yard touchdown pass to Ward. With 4:34 remaining in the half, former-Steelers' kicker [[Kris Brown]] converted a 34-yard field goal. Pittsburgh led the game 21<U+2013>3 as time expired on the first half.<ref name=PbP1>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=29536&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=REG1&override=true|title= Week One GameCenter|accessdate=2008-09-08 |work= Play-by-play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-09-07}}</ref><ref name=Gbook1>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/29536/PIT_Gamebook.pdf|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2008-09-08 |work= Houston Texans At Pittsburgh Steelers|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-09-07|format=PDF}}</ref>

In the second half, Parker scored his third touchdown of the game<U+2014>surpassing his touchdown total for the entire 2007 season<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/players/careerstats?id=PAR468944|title= Willie Parker|accessdate=2008-09-08 |work= Career Stats|publisher= NFL.com}}</ref><U+2014>and was named the AFC offensive player of the week for his performance.<ref>{{cite news |first= Ed|last= Bouchette|title= Steelers' Parker named AFC offensive player of the week|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08254/910983-66.stm?cmpid=sports.xml|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 2008-09-10|accessdate=2008-09-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first= Scott|last= Brown|title= Parker earns AFC honors|url= http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/sports/steelers/s_587646.html?source=rss&feed=3|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Tribune-Review''|date= 2008-09-11|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> Pittsburgh's defense held Houston to six&nbsp;yards on their ensuing drive and the Steelers drove 80&nbsp;yards to take a 35<U+2013>3 lead. The Texans scored two touchdowns in the final quarter, but Pittsburgh's [[James Harrison (American football)|James Harrison]] led the team with three sacks<U+2014>forcing a fumble on the third<U+2014>and the Steelers won their first game of the season.<ref name=PbP1/><ref name=Gbook1/>

===Week 2: at Cleveland Browns===
{| class="toccolours collapsible collapsed" width=100% align="center"
|-
! style="background:#FFD700"|Week Two: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. Cleveland Browns <U+2014> Game information
|-
|
{{col-begin}}
