{{Linescore Amfootball|
|Road='''Steelers'''
|R1=0
|R2=7
|R3=3
|R4=0
|Home=Browns
|H1=0
|H2=0
|H3=3
|H4=3
}}
The Steelers entered their first matchup with the [[2008 Cleveland Browns season|Cleveland Browns]] having won 15 of the last 16&nbsp;games between the two teams.<ref>{{cite news |first= Teresa|last= Varley|title= Rivalry remains strong|url= http://news.steelers.com/article/95938/|publisher= PittsburghSteelers.com|date= 2008-09-12|accessdate=2008-09-14}}</ref> Ben Roethlisberger started the game despite missing practice time during the week due to a shoulder injury suffered in Week One.<ref>{{cite news |first= Gerry|last= Dulac|title= Steelers Notebook: Roethlisberger limited in practice, should play|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08256/911635-66.stm?cmpid=sports.xml|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 2008-09-12|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> The Steelers' defense held the Browns to 16&nbsp;yards on their first four drives, as the teams played to a scoreless tie after the first quarter. After a [[Bryant McFadden]] interception the Steelers drove 70&nbsp;yards and Roethlisberger connected with Hines Ward for their third touchdown combination of the season. Cleveland responded with a 14&nbsp;play, 71&nbsp;yard drive, but [[Troy Polamalu]] intercepted a Cleveland pass as time expired in the first half solidifying Pittsburgh's seven point halftime lead.<ref name=PbP2>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=29558&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=REG2&override=true|title= Week Two GameCenter|accessdate=2008-09-15 |work= Play-by-play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-09-14}}</ref><ref name=Week2Sum>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/29558/CLV_Gamebook.pdf|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2008-09-15 |work= Pittsburgh Steelers At Cleveland Browns|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-09-15|format=PDF}}</ref>

A 48-yard pass from Roethlisberger to [[Santonio Holmes]] and a 48-yard field goal from Jeff Reed on the team's second drive of the second half brought the score to 10<U+2013>0. The Browns' [[Phil Dawson]] converted two consecutive field goals, to pull Cleveland within four points with 3:21&nbsp;remaining. After a fourth down stop, Cleveland's offense took over with 26&nbsp;seconds remaining, but failed to gain yardage as time expired.<ref name=PbP2/><ref name=Week2Sum/> With the win, the Steelers increased their win streak over the Browns to 10&nbsp;consecutive games<U+2014>the longest current winning streak over a single opponent in the NFL.<ref>{{cite news |author= Associated Press |title= Sore shoulder doesn't bother Roethlisberger; Steelers hold Browns without a TD|url= http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=280914005|work= Fast Facts|publisher= ESPN.com|date= 2008-09-14|accessdate=2008-09-15}}</ref>

===Week 3: at Philadelphia Eagles===
{| class="toccolours collapsible collapsed" width=100% align="center"
