{{Linescore Amfootball|
|Road=Ravens
|R1=3
|R2=10
|R3=0
|R4=7
|R5=0
|Home='''Steelers'''
|H1=3
|H2=0
|H3=14
|H4=3
|H5=3
}}
[[Image:Ravens vs Steelers 2008 MNF.jpg|left|thumb|The Steelers have won 14&nbsp;consecutive Monday night games at home.<ref name=W4mnf/>]]
Donning their [[throwback uniform]]s,<ref>{{cite news |first= Teresa|last= Varley|url= http://news.steelers.com/article/96523/|title= Steelers looking forward to home field advantage|accessdate= 2008-09-26|date= 2008-09-26 |publisher= Steelers.com}}</ref> the Steelers played the [[2008 Baltimore Ravens season|Baltimore Ravens]] in their first [[Monday Night Football|Monday Night]] game of the season. Multiple Steelers starters did not play in the game, due to various injuries.<ref>{{cite news |first= Teresa|last= Varley|title= Parker one of three starters to miss Ravens game|url= http://news.steelers.com/article/96480/|publisher= Steelers.com|date= 2008-09-23|accessdate=2008-09-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first= Ed|last= Bouchette|title= Steelers Parker, Hampton injured, won't play Monday|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08267/914374-66.stm?cmpid=sports.xml|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 2008-09-23|accessdate=2008-09-23}}</ref> After a 3<U+2013>3 first quarter, Baltimore took a ten point lead into half time with a field goal and touchdown pass in the second quarter. Rashard Mendenhall<U+2014>in his first NFL start<ref>{{cite news |author= Associated Press|authorlink= Associated Press|title= Steelers will be without RB Parker, DT Hampton against rival Ravens|url= http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3604561|publisher= [[ESPN.com]]|date= 2008-09-23|accessdate=2008-09-23}}</ref><U+2014>left the game in the third quarter with a season-ending shoulder injury.<ref>{{cite news |author= Associated Press|authorlink= Associated Press|title= Simmons, Mendenhall suffer season-ending injuries|url= http://www.nfl.com/news/story;jsessionid=757598AE57696FB023CE71D128201739?id=09000d5d80b3f4dc&template=with-video&confirm=true|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-09-29|accessdate=2008-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first= Ed|last= Bouchette|title= Steelers Notebook: Top pick, guard on IR, to miss rest of season|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08274/916184-66.stm|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 2008-09-30|accessdate=2008-09-30}}</ref> On Pittsburgh's third drive of the half, Roethlisberger connected with Santonio Holmes for a 38-yard touchdown pass. On the first play of Baltimore's ensuing drive, James Harrison's forced fumble was picked up by LaMarr Woodley and returned 7&nbsp;yards for a touchdown. The two touchdowns within 15&nbsp;seconds took the Steelers from ten points behind to four points ahead. In the final quarter, the Steelers' offense was stopped on the one yard line and Reed kicked his second field goal of the night. Baltimore drove 76&nbsp;yards and tied the game with a touchdown. Neither team was able to score on their final drive as the regulation clock expired.<ref name=PbP4>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=29588&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=REG4&override=true|title= Week Four GameCenter|accessdate=2008-09-30 |work= Play-by-Play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-09-30}}</ref><ref name=W4Sum>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/29588/PIT_Gamebook.pdf|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2008-09-30 |work= Baltimore Ravens At Pittsburgh Steelers|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-09-30|format=PDF}}</ref>

Baltimore won the overtime coin toss and elected to receive. The Ravens started the drive at their own 15&nbsp;yard line. The Steelers held them for no gain on the first two plays and [[Lawrence Timmons]] sacked Flacco on third down. The Steelers took over after a punt and [[Mewelde Moore]] caught a 24&nbsp;yard reception to bring the Steelers to Baltimore's 31-yard line. Jeff Reed converted a 46-yard field goal to win the game for the Steelers.<ref name=PbP4/><ref name=W4Sum/> Reed was named the NFL's special teams player of the week.<ref>{{cite news |first= Gerry|last= Dulac|title= Steelers sign Russell; kicker Reed named player of week|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08275/916465-66.stm?cmpid=sports.xml|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 2008-10-01|accessdate=2008-10-01}}</ref> With the win the Steelers passed the Ravens for first place in the AFC North at 3<U+2013>1, as well as extending their all-time record of 14&nbsp;consecutive home wins on Monday Night Football.<ref name=W4mnf>{{cite news |author= Associated Press |title= Steelers climb back, hang on for OT victory as Ravens lose first of season|url= http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=280929023|publisher= ESPN.com|date= 2008-09-29|accessdate=2008-09-30}}</ref>

===Week 5: at Jacksonville Jaguars===
{| class="toccolours collapsible collapsed" width=100% align="center"
|-
! style="background:#FFD700"|Week Five: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. Jacksonville Jaguars <U+2014> Game information
|-
|
{{col-begin}}
{{col-2}}
*Sunday, October 5 at 8:15 PM EDT (NBC Sunday Night Football)
*'''Game weather:''' 73<U+00B0>F, Cloudy
*'''Referee:''' [[Ron Winter]]
{{col-2}}
*'''Game attendance:''' 65,908 at [[Jacksonville Municipal Stadium]] in [[Jacksonville, Florida]]
