The Steelers' matchup with the [[2008 Jacksonville Jaguars season|Jacksonville Jaguars]]<U+2014>their first since the Jaguars knocked the Steelers out of the [[NFL playoffs, 2007<U+2013>08#AFC: Jacksonville Jaguars 31, Pittsburgh Steelers 29|2007 playoffs]]<U+2014>was featured as the [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]]'s ''Throwback Game of the Week''.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.profootballhof.com/ThrowbackGOW_PIT_at_JAC.jsp|title= Week 5 <U+2013> Steelers at Jaguars |accessdate=2008-10-02 |work= Throwback Game of the Week|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-10-02}}</ref> On the Steelers opening drive, Roethlisberger<U+2014>who missed practice time during the week due to injections for his shoulder<ref>{{cite news |first= Gerry|last= Dulac|title= Big Ben doesn't practice again|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08276/916891-66.stm?cmpid=sports.xml|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 2008-10-02|accessdate=2008-10-02}}</ref><U+2014>was intercepted by [[Rashean Mathis]] who returned the ball 72&nbsp;yards for a touchdown. Pittsburgh responded by driving 71&nbsp;yards, with Heath Miller receiving a 1-yard touchdown pass to tie the game. Jacksonville re-gained the lead on the next drive when [[Maurice Jones-Drew]] ran for a touchdown. Pittsburgh took the lead in the second quarter with two field goals and a 48&nbsp;yard touchdown pass from Roethlisberger to [[Nate Washington]].<ref name=PbP5>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=29601&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=REG5&override=true|title= Week Five GameCenter|accessdate=2008-10-05 |work= Play-by-Play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-10-05}}</ref><ref name=W5Sum>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/29601/JAX_Gamebook.pdf|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2008-10-05|work= Pittsburgh Steelers At Jacksonville Jaguars|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-10-05|format=PDF}}</ref>

Jacksonville scored first in the final quarter with a touchdown pass from [[David Garrard]] to [[Marcedes Lewis]]. The Steelers drove from their 20&nbsp;yard line in the fourth quarter, Ward received an 8-yard touchdown pass to put the Steelers up by 5&nbsp;points with 1:53 remaining in regulation, however, the 2-pt conversion failed.<ref name=PbP5/><ref name=W5Sum/> Roethlisberger received the AFC offensive player of the week award for his 309&nbsp;yard, 3&nbsp;touchdown pass performance, despite having an injured throwing shoulder.<ref>{{cite news |first= Teresa|last= Varley|title= Roethlisberger AFC Offensive Player of the Week|url= http://news.steelers.com/article/97361/|publisher= Steelers.com|date= 2008-10-08|accessdate=2008-10-08}}</ref> The NFL selected the game as the league's Week Five Game of the Week.<ref>{{cite video |date2= 2008-10-10|title= Week 5: Pittsburgh vs. Jacksonville Game of the Week|url= http://www.nfl.com/videos?videoId=09000d5d80b78497|medium= Television production|publisher= [[National Football League]]|location= [[Jacksonville, Florida]]|accessdate=2008-10-10}}</ref>

===Week 6: Bye Week===
The Steelers used their [[Bye (sports)|bye week]] to rest injured players including Brett Keisel, Willie Parker, Jeff Reed, and Ben Roethlisberger.<ref>{{cite news |first= F. Dale|last= Lolley|title= Steelers getting healthy as Parker, Keisel return 
|url= http://www.observer-reporter.com/OR/Story/10-8-Steelers-returning-to-health|publisher= ''[[Observer-Reporter]]''|date= 2008-10-08|accessdate=2008-10-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first= Ed|last= Bouchette|title= Injury list could trim with help of open date|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08282/918208-66.stm|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 2008-10-08|accessdate=2008-10-08}}</ref> 
The team hosted an event to honor wounded veterans of [[Operation Enduring Freedom]] and [[Iraq War|Operation Iraqi Freedom]] at Heinz Field. Players signed autographs and held on-field drills with the veterans, while soldiers and Marines spoke of their experiences.<ref>{{cite news |first= Teresa|last= Varley|title= Saying thanks to true heroes|url= http://news.steelers.com/article/97258/|publisher= PittsburghSteelers.com|date= 2008-10-08|accessdate=2008-10-08}}</ref> [[Chris Hoke]], who attended the event said, "These are the people who fight for us to have our freedom and be who we are as Americans. To come out here and spend a couple hours with them and hear their stories is unbelievable. There's nothing better than this."<ref>{{cite news |first= Karen|last= Price|title= Steelers host wounded vets at Heinz Field|url= http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/sports/steelers/s_592163.html|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Tribune-Review''|date= 2008-10-08|accessdate=2008-10-08}}</ref>

