Both the Steelers and [[Indianapolis Colts]] drove more than 60&nbsp;yards on their opening offensive drives, each scored a touchdown to bring the score to 7<U+2013>7 after the first quarter. A Steelers 42-yard [[Flea flicker (American football)|flea flicker]] advanced the ball to the 2&nbsp;yard line. On the following play Mewelde Moore scored his second touchdown of the game. The Steelers extended their lead to ten, but an interception with 1:30 remaining in the half led to a Colts touchdown<U+2014>bringing the halftime score to 17<U+2013>14.<ref name=PbP10>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=29668&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=REG10&override=true|title= Week Ten GameCenter|accessdate=2008-11-09 |work= Play-by-Play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-11-09}}</ref><ref name=W10Sum>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/29668/PIT_Gamebook.pdf|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2008-11-09|work= Indianapolis Colts At Pittsburgh Steelers|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-11-09|format=PDF}}</ref>

The Colts kicked a 36-yard field goal in the third quarter to tie the game at 17. A Steelers field goal in the final quarter gave them a three point lead. The Colts scored on Peyton Manning's third touchdown pass of the game to take the lead with 3:10 remaining in regulation. The Steelers drove from their own 27&nbsp;yard line, but were unable to score.<ref name=PbP10/><ref name=W10Sum/>

===Week 11: vs. San Diego Chargers===
{| class="toccolours collapsible collapsed" width=100% align="center"
