The [[2008 Dallas Cowboys season|Dallas Cowboys]] and the Steelers held each other scoreless in the first quarter. Troy Polamalu intercepted a pass in his fourth consecutive game, overall he led the league with seven interceptions.<ref>{{cite news |first= Ed|last= Bouchette|title= Steelers Notebook: Harrison ties sack record, but wants more|curly=y |url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08343/933652-66.stm?cmpid=sports.xml|work= Quick hits|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 8 December 2008|accessdate=8 December 2008}}</ref> The Steelers scored first on a 24-yard field goal from Jeff Reed with 2:44 remaining in the second quarter. The Cowboys converted a 44-yard field goal as time expired on the first half to tie the game at 3<U+2013>3.<ref name=PbP14>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=29733&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=REG14&override=true|title= Week Fourteen GameCenter|accessdate=2008-12-07 |work= Play-by-Play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-12-07}}</ref><ref name=W14Sum>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/29733/PIT_Gamebook.pdf|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2008-12-07|work= Dallas Cowboys at Pittsburgh Steelers|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-12-07|format=PDF}}</ref> 

A [[Tony Romo]] touchdown pass in the third quarter gave the Cowboys their first lead of the game. The lead was extended when [[Nick Folk]] converted his second field goal of the day, putting the Cowboys up 13<U+2013>3 as the game entered the final quarter. Reed converted his second field goal of the game, bringing the Steelers within seven points with 7:20 remaining in regulation. On the Steelers next drive, Ben Roethelisberger threw a touchdown pass to Heath Miller<U+2014>tying the game with 2:10 remaining. [[Deshea Townsend]] intercepted Romo's next pass and returned the ball 25&nbsp;yards, scoring a touchdown to give the Steelers a seven point lead, which they held to the end of the game.<ref name=PbP14/><ref name=W14Sum/>

===Week 15: at Baltimore Ravens===
{| class="toccolours collapsible collapsed" width=100% align="center"
|-
! style="background:#FFD700"|Week Fifteen: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. Baltimore Ravens <U+2014> Game information
|-
|
{{col-begin}}
