Pittsburgh entered their final road game of the regular season with a chance to surpass the [[2008 Tennessee Titans season|Tennessee Titans]] for the top seed in the AFC.<ref>{{cite news |first= Ed|last= Bouchette|title= Steelers take Ravens, 13-9|url= http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08349/935181-66.stm?cmpid=sports.xml|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''|date= 14 December 2008|accessdate=15 December 2008}}</ref> The Steelers and the Titans were scoreless after the first quarter, when Tennessee took a 3<U+2013>0 lead on the second play of the second quarter. [[Justin Gage]]'s 34-yard reception later in the quarter extended the lead to 10<U+2013>0. Pittsburgh's Santonio Holmes also received a touchdown pass in the second quarter, bringing the halftime score to 10<U+2013>7.<ref name=PbP16>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/29761/TEN_Gamebook.pdf|format=PDF|title= Week Sixteen GameCenter|accessdate=2008-12-21|work= Play-by-Play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-12-21}}</ref><ref name=W16Sum>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=29761&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=REG16&override=true|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2008-12-21|work= Pittsburgh Steelers at Tennessee Titans|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2008-12-21|format=PDF}}</ref>

In the second half, Ben Roethlisberger threw his second touchdown pass of the game<U+2014>to Hines Ward<U+2014>to give the Steelers their only lead of the game. After a 21-yard touchdown run on Tennessee's ensuing drive, the Titans entered the final quarter with a three point lead. The Titans scored two touchdowns in the final quarter, and the Steelers were unable overcome two Roethelisberger fumbles and two interceptions throughout the game.<ref name=PbP16/><ref name=W16Sum/>

===Week 17: vs. Cleveland Browns===
{| class="toccolours collapsible collapsed" width=100% align="center"
