*PIT - Parker - 24 attempts, 47 yards
;Leading receivers
*BAL - [[Ray Rice|Rice]] - 3 receptions, 43 yards
*PIT - Holmes - 2 receptions, 70 yards, 1 touchdown
;Leading tacklers
*BAL - [[Ray Lewis (American football)|Lewis]], [[Bart Scott|Scott]] - 6 tackles each
*PIT - [[Ryan Clark (American football)|Clark]] - 8 tackles, 1 forced fumble
{{col-end}}
|}
{{Linescore Amfootball|
|Road=Ravens
|R1=0
|R2=7
|R3=0
|R4=7
|Home='''Steelers'''
|H1=6
|H2=7
|H3=3
|H4=7
}}
Pittsburgh hosted the Baltimore Ravens<U+2014>who defeated the Miami Dolphins and Tennessee Titans in the Wild Card and Divisional rounds respectively<U+2014>for the AFC Championship Game.<ref name=PostSch/> During the week before the game, Pittsburgh mayor [[Luke Ravenstahl]] temporarily changed his name to Luke Steelerstahl in order to remove the "Raven". Though the change was not official the mayor did comment that "As soon as [he] heard [the idea], [he] thought it was a great idea."<ref>{{cite news |title= Mayor's new name: Steelerstahl|url= http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/playoffs2008/news/story?id=3832512|publisher= ESPN.com|date= 14 January 2009|accessdate=15 January 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first= Jeremy|last= Boren|title= Mayor changes name to 'Steelerstahl'|url= http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/news/cityregion/s_607140.html?source=rss&feed=1|publisher= ''Pittsburgh Tribune-Review''|date= 14 January 2009|accessdate=15 January 2009}}</ref>

Pittsburgh scored the game's first points, with Jeff Reed converting on field goals from 34 and 42&nbsp;yards in the first quarter. Santonio Holmes received a pass from Ben Roethlisberger in the second quarter and ran for a touchdown to give the Steelers a 13<U+2013>0 lead. Baltimore's Willis McGahee ran into the endzone for a touchdown with 2:44 remaining in the second quarter<U+2014>bringing the halftime score to 13<U+2013>7. Reed converted his third field goal of the game from 46&nbsp;yards in the third quarter. McGahee scored his second touchdown of the game with 9:32 remaining in the final quarter bringing the Ravens within two points. Troy Polamalu intercepted a pass from Joe Flacco and returned it 40&nbsp;yards to score the final touchdown of the game, giving Pittsburgh a 23<U+2013>14 victory.<ref name=PbP19>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/playbyplay?game_id=54464&displayPage=tab_play_by_play&season=2008&week=POST20&override=true|title= Divisional round GameCenter|accessdate=2009-01-18|work= Play-by-Play|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2009-01-18}}</ref><ref name=W19Sum>{{cite web |url= http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/54464/PIT_Gamebook.pdf|title= National Football League Game Summary|accessdate=2009-01-18|work=Baltimore Ravens at Pittsburgh Steelers|publisher= NFL.com|date= 2009-01-18|format=PDF}}</ref>

=== Super Bowl: at Arizona Cardinals ===
{{main|Super Bowl XLIII}}
